(90, 60, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n<div class="interior-content">\n  <div id="mainColumn" class="services">\n\n<h1>Economic Development</h1>\n<div id="callout">\n  <h2>Our Experience</h2>\n  <p>Decatur County, Indiana, had the opportunity of a lifetime in 2006. All they had to do was present the winning case for why their area was the most advantageous location for a new Honda Motors automobile assembly plant. And like most economic development projects, responding quickly was essential to stay in the running.</p>\n  <p><a href="/services/our-experience/winning-a-honda-plant-for-decatur-county">Read More &raquo;</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n<p>Quick deadlines? We&#8217;re used to them at UMBAUGH. In the world of economic development, quickly having the right response makes the difference between securing economic development for your area and watching it go elsewhere.</p>\n<p>With most local governments&#8217; tax revenues decreasing, economic development is the key to growing your tax base. But it&#8217;s not wise to say yes to every economic development opportunity that comes your way. You need to run the numbers, consider alternatives and make informed decisions about what&#8217;s right for your community to avoid overburdening your existing taxpayers or putting your investment at risk. UMBAUGH helps communities evaluate and structure economic development packages to produce long-term financial gain &#8211; not pain, using tax increment financing, tax abatement and the right balance of a variety of economic development tools.</p>\n<p>UMBAUGH&#8217;s economic development services continue long after the deal is done. We provide accurate financial data and reporting so you can make informed decisions about releasing tax revenue and leveraging your investment to generate additional development.</p>\n</p>\n<div id="services-table">\n  <h2>Our Services for Economic Development</h2>\n  <p><strong>Attracting and Retaining Businesses</strong> &#8211; Your job boils down to this: How do I attract new business to our area? And how do I keep existing businesses satisfied and economically healthy? The financial package may make the live-or-die difference between businesses choosing your site or someplace else. At the same time, you have this gnawing fear about giving away too much. UMBAUGH can help you make good decisions with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Economic Impact Analysis</li>\n    <li>Tax Abatement Alternatives</li>\n    <li>Tax Increment (TIF) Feasibility Studies</li>\n    <li>Tax Impact Analysis</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Assistance with the Creation of TIF Areas</li>\n    <li>Developing Funding Alternatives</li>\n    <li>Developing Incentive Packages</li>\n    <li>Financial Presentations to Elected Officials and the Public</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Bond Issuance</strong> &#8211; You don&#8217;t issue bonds every day, and you&#8217;ve got to get it right. The stakes are too high to risk a mistake or miss an opportunity to save. Since UMBAUGH is an independent advisor, our only priority is doing what&#8217;s best for the local governments we represent.  We can provide:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Official Statements and Bond Sale Preparations</li>\n    <li>Presentations to Bond Ratings Agencies</li>\n    <li>Evaluation of Bond Insurance Proposals</li>\n    <li>Competitive Bond Sales and Electronic Bidding Services</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Negotiated Bond Sales and Private Placements</li>\n    <li>Coordination of Bond Closings</li>\n    <li>Assistance to the Trustee bank</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Post Issuance</strong> &#8211; Unfortunately, paperwork does not go away after the bonds are sold. You as the bond issuer have a great deal of responsibility for monitoring your TIF revenue, reporting and compliance, at a time when you&#8217;d much rather celebrate the benefits of your hard-won economic development project. UMBAUGH can take those worries off your plate as well with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Monitoring of Tax Increment Revenues</li>\n    <li>In-Progress Construction Reports</li>\n    <li>Arbitrage Rebate Calculations</li>\n    <li>Continuing Disclosure Filings</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Post Issuance Tax Compliance</li>\n    <li>Escrow Verifications</li>\n    <li>Parity Reports</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div class="two-col-list">\n  <h3>Representative Projects</h3>\n  <p>UMBAUGH has completed over a thousand bond issues ranging from $50,000 to over $500 million.</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Boone County, IN - Duke Anson Development and MEDCO </li>\n    <li>Bowling Green, KY - Downtown Signature Project, a public-private redevelopment project </li>\n    <li>Carmel, IN - Performing Arts Center and City Center Project </li>\n    <li>Decatur County, IN - Honda manufacturing facility </li>\n    <li>Delaware County, IN - Magna Powertrain manufacturing facility </li>\n    <li>Gibson County, IN - Toyota truck manufacturing facility </li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Jeffersonville, IN - MedVenture medical device manufacturing facility </li>\n    <li>Noblesville, IN - Hamilton Town Center, an open-air, lifestyle shopping center </li>\n    <li>Noblesville, IN - SMC manufacturing facility </li>\n    <li>Plainfield, IN - Metropolis, an open-air, lifestyle shopping center </li>\n    <li>Spencer County, IN - A.K. Steel manufacturing facility </li>\n    <li>White County, IN - Wind turbines</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div id="wide-callout">\n  <h2>Cash Advisory Serivces</h2>\n  <p><a href="http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com" target="_blank">Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC</a> was developed as an independent business entity to help create<br />\n    structured investment programs for our client''s bond proceeds and operating funds.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n  </div><!-- end div #mainColumn -->\n  <div id="sideColumn"> \n    <div id="nav_menu-4" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n      <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n        <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n          <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/services">Our Services</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n	<h2>Latest News goes here</h2>\n			</div><!-- end DIV #sideColumn --> \n		</div><!-- end div .interior-content --> \n	</div><!-- end div #wrapper --> \n{embed=''includes/footer''}'),
(91, 62, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n<div class="interior-content">\n  <div id="mainColumn" class="services">\n\n<h1>Local Governments</h1>\n<div id="callout">\n  <h2>Our Experience</h2>\n  <p>"Business as it used to run in the counties can no longer happen," says Ken Paust, county commissioner in Wayne County, Indiana. <br />\n    He''s speaking of how local governments in Indiana were affected when property tax caps began taking effect just as a general economic downturn reduced other revenue sources.</p>\n  <p><a href="/services/our-experience/a-financial-road-map-for-wayne-county-in">Read More &raquo;</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n<p>Operating a local governmental unit always has challenges and opportunities. You may be looking for new efficiencies, projecting changes in tax revenue, finding new revenue sources, working on long-range planning, funding buildings and improvements, or structuring the most advantageous economic development package. Our years of experience in helping others in similar situations make us uniquely qualified to help you today &#8212; and with tomorrow&#8217;s challenges.</p>\n</p>\n<div id="services-table">\n  <h2>Our Services for Local Government</h2>\n  <p><strong>Financial Management</strong> &#8211; No one who works in local government would say that financial management is &#8220;simple.&#8221;   Your constituents never think about how time consuming your day-to-day tasks are.  Umbaugh can help you with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Audit Preparation</li>\n    <li>CAFR Preparation</li>\n    <li>Financial Reporting</li>\n    <li>Tax Revenue Analysis and Management</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Budget Preparation Assistance</li>\n    <li>Comprehensive Financial Planning</li>\n    <li>GASB 34 Compliance</li>\n    <li>User Fee Development</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>As you look for every <strong>cost savings and efficiency</strong>, we can also provide:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Consolidation Planning and Implementation</li>\n    <li>Negotiating Inter-Governmental Agreements</li>\n    <li>Performance Management Studies</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>If you are considering a new accounting system, let us relieve your nightmares and worry of system selection (What if it doesn&#8217;t work?  What if we lose our data?) with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Accounting Systems Consulting</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Capital Planning</strong> &#8211; Every unit of government has projects that need to be done – and equipment that needs to be upgraded or replaced.  It&#8217;s tempting to defer projects and delay expenses, but that could catch up to you someday with a big bill – or a service failure.  We all know it&#8217;s better to plan ahead.  Umbaugh can help you with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Debt Management Studies</li>\n    <li>Project Planning and Financial Development</li>\n    <li>Refinancing of Existing Debt</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Long-Range Capital Planning and Implementation</li>\n    <li>Developing and Evaluating Funding Alternatives</li>\n    <li>Financial Presentations to Elected Officials and the Public</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Bond Issuance</strong> &#8211; Bond issues are not something you do every day, and you&#8217;ve got to get it right. The stakes are literally too high to risk a mistake or miss an opportunity to save. Since Umbaugh is an independent advisor, our only priority is doing what&#8217;s best for the local governments we represent. We can provide:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Official Statements and Bond Sale Preparations</li>\n    <li>Presentations to Bond Ratings Agencies</li>\n    <li>Evaluation of Bond Insurance Proposals</li>\n    <li>Competitive Bond Sales and Electronic Bidding Services</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Negotiated Bond Sales and Private Placements</li>\n    <li>Coordination of Bond Closings</li>\n    <li>Assistance to the Trustee Bank</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Post Issuance</strong> &#8211; Unfortunately, the paperwork does not go away after the bonds are sold.  You as the bond issuer have a great deal of responsibility for reporting and compliance, at a time when you&#8217;d much rather be paying attention to your bond-funded project.  Umbaugh can take those worries off your plate as well with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>In-Progress Construction Reports</li>\n    <li>Arbitrage Rebate Calculations</li>\n    <li>Continuing Disclosure Filings</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Post Issuance Compliance</li>\n    <li>Escrow Verifications</li>\n    <li>Parity Reports</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div class="two-col-list">\n  <h3>Representative Projects</h3>\n  <p>UMBAUGH has completed over a thousand bond issues ranging from $50,000 to over $500 million.</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>City of Greensburg, IN </li>\n    <li>City of Mishawaka, IN </li>\n    <li>City of Plymouth, IN </li>\n    <li>City of South Bend, IN </li>\n    <li>Elkhart County, IN </li>\n    <li>Jasper County, IN </li>\n    <li>Kosciusko County, IN </li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Marshall County, IN </li>\n    <li>Ovid Township, MI </li>\n    <li>Starke County, IN </li>\n    <li>Wayne County, IN </li>\n    <li>White County, IN </li>\n    <li>Whitley County, IN</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div id="wide-callout">\n  <h2>Cash Advisory Serivces</h2>\n  <p><a href="http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com" target="_blank">Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC</a> was developed as an independent business entity to help create<br />\n    structured investment programs for our client''s bond proceeds and operating funds.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n  </div><!-- end div #mainColumn -->\n  <div id="sideColumn"> \n    <div id="nav_menu-4" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n      <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n        <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n          <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/services">Our Services</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n	<h2>Latest News goes here</h2>\n			</div><!-- end DIV #sideColumn --> \n		</div><!-- end div .interior-content --> \n	</div><!-- end div #wrapper --> \n{embed=''includes/footer''}'),
(92, 57, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title="Our Services"}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n  <div class="interior-content">\n    <div id="mainColumn" class="services">\n      <h1>Our Services</h1>\n      <div id="callout">\n        <h2>Our Areas of Expertise</h2>\n        <div class="dotted-seperator" style="width: 200px;"></div>\n        <ul>\n          <li>&raquo; <a href="/services/government">Local Government</a></li>\n          <li>&raquo; <a href="/services/utilities">Utilities</a></li>\n          <li>&raquo; <a href="/services/development">Economic Development</a></li>\n          <li>&raquo; <a href="/services/schools">Schools</a></li>\n          <li>&raquo; <a href="/services/libraries">Libraries</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n      <p>Our comprehensive services are tailored to each client''s special needs, offering guidance and assistance from inception to project completion, financial analysis and long-term planning. Because we are independent advisors, we are objective in analyzing, planning and structuring creative solutions for many types of projects.</p>\n      <div id="wide-callout">\n        <h2>Cash Advisory Services</h2>\n        <p><a href="http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com/">Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC</a> was developed as an independent business entity to help create structured investment programs for our client''s bond proceeds and operating funds.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <!-- end div #mainColumn -->\n    <div id="sideColumn">\n      <div id="nav_menu-4" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n        <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n          <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n            <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/about">About Us</a></li>\n            <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n            <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div id="category-content" class="widget widget_categoryContent">\n        <h2 class="widget-title"> Latest News </h2>\n        <ul>\n          {exp:channel:entries channel="news" limit="2"}\n          <li> <a href="/latest-news/{url_title}">{title}</a> {exp:word_limit total="20"}{news_body}{/exp:word_limit}\n            <p class="readmore"><a href="/latest-news/{url_title}">Read More &raquo;</a></p>\n          </li>\n          {/exp:channel:entries}\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <!-- end DIV #sideColumn --> \n  </div>\n  <!-- end div .interior-content --> \n</div>\n<!-- end div #wrapper --> \n{embed=''includes/footer''}'),
(93, 58, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n<div class="interior-content">\n  <div id="mainColumn" class="services">\n\n<h1>Libraries</h1>\n<div id="callout">\n  <h2>Our Experience</h2>\n  <p>In response to growth and space needs, the Allen County Library, based in Fort Wayne, Indiana, renovated and expanded its main library and upgraded its branch libraries from 2002 to 2007.  Umbaugh assisted with the $84 million bond issue to fund those projects.</p>\n  <p><a href="/services/our-experience/allen-county-public-library-renovation-and-expansion">Read More &raquo;</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n<p>Libraries have needs that are different from other units of government.  UMBAUGH financial consultants are experienced with library projects &#8211; from bond issues to property tax projections. We consider it very fulfilling to help libraries through all the financial aspects of completing a project.</p>\n</p>\n<div id="services-table">\n  <h2>Our Services for Libraries</h2>\n  <p>Most library managers went into that line of work because they really love books and knowledge &#8211; not because they enjoy finances or managing facilities! But financial management and keeping your facilities and technology up to the standards today&#8217;s library users expect come with the management job. And like other local governmental units these days, most libraries are grappling with how to operate on reduced revenue.</p>\n  <p><strong>Financial Management</strong> &#8211; You can spend more time with your beloved books (or electronic media!) when you let UMBAUGH assist you with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Accounting Systems Design, Implementation and Training</li>\n    <li>Audit Preparation and Financial Reporting</li>\n    <li>Budget Preparation Assistance</li>\n    <li>Comprehensive Financial Planning</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>GASB 34 Compliance</li>\n    <li>Performance Management Studies</li>\n    <li>Tax Revenue Analysis and Management</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Capital Planning</strong> &#8211; Library building or major renovation projects may happen just once in your career. They are truly different experiences from your normal operations, requiring specialized skills. UMBAUGH can help with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Debt Management Studies</li>\n    <li>Long-Range Capital Planning and Implementation</li>\n    <li>Project Planning and Financial Development</li>\n    <li>Developing and Evaluating Funding Alternatives</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Refinancing of Existing Debt</li>\n    <li>Referendum Preparation</li>\n    <li>Financial Presentations to Elected Officials and the Public</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Bond Issuance</strong> &#8211; Bond issues are not something you do every day, and you&#8217;ve got to get it right. The stakes are too high to risk a mistake or miss an opportunity to save. Since UMBAUGH is an independent advisor, our only priority is doing what&#8217;s best for the libraries we represent.  We can provide:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Official Statements and Bond Sale Preparations</li>\n    <li>Presentations to Bond Ratings Agencies</li>\n    <li>Evaluation of Bond Insurance Proposals</li>\n    <li>Competitive Bond Sales and Electronic Bidding Services</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Negotiated Bond Sales and Private Placements</li>\n    <li>Coordination of Bond Closings</li>\n    <li>Assistance to the Trustee Bank</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Post Issuance</strong> &#8211; Unfortunately, the paperwork does not go away after the bonds are sold. You as the bond issuer have a great deal of responsibility for reporting and compliance, at a time when you&#8217;d much rather be paying attention to your bond-funded project. UMBAUGH can take those worries off your plate as well with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>In-Progress Construction Reports</li>\n    <li>Arbitrage Rebate Calculations</li>\n    <li>Continuing Disclosure Filings</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Post Issuance Tax Compliance</li>\n    <li>Escrow Verifications</li>\n    <li>Parity Reports</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong> </strong></p>\n</div>\n<div class="two-col-list">\n  <h3>Representative Projects</h3>\n  <p>UMBAUGH has completed over a thousand bond issues ranging from $50,000 to over $500 million.</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Allen County Public Library, Fort Wayne, IN </li>\n    <li>Capital Area District Library, MI </li>\n    <li>Carmel-Clay Public Library, Carmel, IN </li>\n    <li>Culver-Union Township Public Library, Culver, IN </li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Indianapolis-Marion County Public Library, Indianapolis, IN </li>\n    <li>Johnson County Public Library, Franklin, IN </li>\n    <li>Peabody Public Library, Columbia City, Lansing, IN</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div id="wide-callout">\n  <h2>Cash Advisory Serivces</h2>\n  <p><a href="http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com" target="_blank">Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC</a> was developed as an independent business entity to help create<br />\n    structured investment programs for our client''s bond proceeds and operating funds.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n  </div><!-- end div #mainColumn -->\n  <div id="sideColumn"> \n    <div id="nav_menu-4" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n      <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n        <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n          <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/services">Our Services</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n	<h2>Latest News goes here</h2>\n			</div><!-- end DIV #sideColumn --> \n		</div><!-- end div .interior-content --> \n	</div><!-- end div #wrapper --> \n{embed=''includes/footer''}'),
(94, 64, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n  <div class="interior-content">\n    <div id="mainColumn" class="wide">\n    	{if segment_3 ==""}\n              <h1>Our Experience</h1>\n              <p>How do you describe in a list of services all the steps it takes to  assemble an economic development package just right for your community?  How do you briefly explain what it takes to start with just the need for  a new school building and get it financed and built? You can&#8217;t. Every  project is different.</p>\n              <p>You can, however, learn from the experiences of others. In the Umbaugh case studies below see how we helped:</p>\n              <ul>\n                <li>save more than $141 million for one school district&#8217;s taxpayers,</li>\n                <li>identify $2 million a year in annual efficiencies for one group of municipal utilities,</li>\n                <li>secure the right economic development arrangements to lure a Honda plant,</li>\n                <li>finance an entire series of library renovations, and</li>\n                <li>improve the financial outlook for countless units of local government.</li>\n              </ul>\n              {exp:channel:entries channel="our_experience"}\n              <div class="news-story">\n                <h2><a href="{site_url}services/our-experience/{url_title}">{title}</a></h2>\n                <span class="date">Project Leader: {our_experience_author}</span><br />\n                <p>{exp:word_limit total="100"}{our_experience_body}{/exp:word_limit}</p>\n                <p class="readmore"><a href="{site_url}services/our-experience/{url_title}">Read More &raquo;</a><br/>\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              {/exp:channel:entries}\n		{/if}\n		{if segment_3 !=""}\n              {exp:channel:entries channel="our_experience"}\n              <h1>{title}</h1>\n              <div class="news-story"> <span class="date">Project Leader: {our_experience_author}</span><br />\n                <p>{our_experience_body}</p>\n              </div>\n              {/exp:channel:entries}\n	{/if}\n       </div><!--end #mainColumn  -->\n    <div id="sideColumn">\n      <div id="nav_menu-5" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n        <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n          <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n            <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/about">More About Us</a></li>\n            <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n            <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </div><!-- end #menu-sidebar-container-->\n      </div><!-- end #nav_menu-->\n    </div><!-- end #sideColumn-->\n  </div><!--end .interior-content --> \n</div><!--end .wrapper --> \n\n{embed=''includes/footer''} '),
(95, 63, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n\n<div class="wrapper">\n  <div class="interior-content">\n    <div id="mainColumn" class="wide">\n      <h1>Our Library</h1>\n      <p>We love to share our expertise!  Umbaugh representatives frequently  speak before seminars, conferences and government hearings to help even  the experts stay current during these changing times for local  governments and finances. In this section you&#8217;ll find presentations, timely  articles from past issues of Footnotes and even a white paper or two.   (Don&#8217;t let the term &#8216;white paper&#8217; scare you; it&#8217;s technical, but  understandable, information.)</p>\n      <p>Check this section often – we&#8217;ll update it often.</p>\n      <p>If you&#8217;d like to schedule a presentation tailored to  your group – or if you don&#8217;t find the topic you&#8217;re looking for, please  call us at (888-516-9594) and we&#8217;ll find the person or information you&#8217;re  looking for.</p>\n      <ul class="links">\n	{exp:channel:entries channel="our_library"}\n		<li>\n			<a href="{library_item_upload}">{title}</a><br />\n		</li>\n	{/exp:channel:entries}\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n    <div id="sideColumn">\n      <div id="nav_menu-6" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n        <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n          <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n            <li ><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/about">More About Us</a></li>\n            <li><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n            <li><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--wrapper-->\n\n{embed=''includes/footer''}'),
(96, 61, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n<div class="interior-content">\n  <div id="mainColumn" class="services">\n\n\n<h1>Schools</h1>\n<div id="callout">\n  <h2>Our Experience</h2>\n  <p>Indianapolis Public Schools embarked on a plan in 2001 to improve its school buildings in what has become the largest school construction program in the state of Indiana. Umbaugh has advised the district throughout the process for a total of $693 million in bond issues.</p>\n  <p><a href="/services/our-experience/umbaugh-advises-indianapolis-public-schools-on-indianas-largest-school-cons">Read More &raquo;</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n<p>At UMBAUGH, we don&#8217;t represent both sides of the table. We represent you as a school district. Our independence from the bond underwriting assures you of the greatest objectivity in analyzing, determining and planning &#8211; whether that&#8217;s for capital improvements or operating funds.</p>\n<p>We quickly respond to your needs. At public hearings, we calmly, accurately and professionally answer all the financial questions your constituents &#8211; and your board &#8211; will have.</p>\n</p>\n<div id="services-table">\n  <h2>Our Services for Schools</h2>\n  <p><strong>Financial Management</strong> &#8211; As a school superintendent or business manager, you create and manage a budget so complex it could perplex a Fortune 500 CEO. Every day, you deal with multiple funding streams from federal, state and local governments, grants and other revenue sources, each with its own set of reporting requirements. Let UMBAUGH ease the strain with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Accounting Systems Design, Implementation and Training</li>\n    <li>Analytical Cost Studies</li>\n    <li>Audit Preparation and Financial Reporting</li>\n    <li>Budget Preparation and Assistance</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Comprehensive Financial Planning</li>\n    <li>GASB 34 Compliance</li>\n    <li>Performance Management Studies</li>\n    <li>Tax Revenue Analysis and Management</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Capital Planning</strong> &#8211; Facilities are always a challenge. If your enrollment&#8217;s growing, you need more. If your buildings are old, you need to modernize for technology, replace infrastructure and save energy. And, oh yes, you need the support of your constitents to make that happen, which requires a clear financial plan. UMBAUGH can help you with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Debt Management Studies</li>\n    <li>Long-Range Capital Planning and Implementation</li>\n    <li>Project Planning and Financial Development</li>\n    <li>Developing and Evaluating Funding Alternatives</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Refinancing Existing Debt</li>\n    <li>Referendum Preparation</li>\n    <li>Financial Presentations to Elected Officials and the Public</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Bond Issuance</strong> &#8211; You don&#8217;t issue bonds every day, but they are getting more common as schools meet facility needs and raise revenue for operating costs.  Either way, you&#8217;ve got to get it right. The stakes are too high to risk a mistake or miss an opportunity to save. Since UMBAUGH is an independent advisor, our only priority is doing what&#8217;s best for the local governments we represent. We can provide:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Official Statements and Bond Sale Preparations</li>\n    <li>Presentations to Bond Ratings Agencies</li>\n    <li>Evaluation of Bond Insurance Proposals</li>\n    <li>Competitive Bond Sales and Electronic Bidding Services</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Negotiated Bond Sales and Private Placements</li>\n    <li>Coordination of Bond Closings</li>\n    <li>Assistance to the Trustee bank</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Post Issuance</strong> &#8211; Unfortunately, paperwork does not go away after the bonds are sold. You as the bond issuer have a great deal of responsibility for reporting and compliance, at a time when you&#8217;d much rather pay attention to your bond-funded project. UMBAUGH can take those worries off your plate as well with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>In-Progress Construction Reports</li>\n    <li>Arbitrage Rebate Calculations</li>\n    <li>Continuing Disclosure Filings</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Post Issuance Tax Compliance</li>\n    <li>Escrow Verifications</li>\n    <li>Parity Reports</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div class="two-col-list">\n  <h3>Representative Projects</h3>\n  <p>UMBAUGH has completed over a thousand bond issues ranging from $50,000 to over $500 million.</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Allen Park Public Schools, Allen Park, MI </li>\n    <li>Bay City Public Schools, Bay City, MI </li>\n    <li>Brighton Area Schools, Brighton, MI </li>\n    <li>Carrollton Public School, Carrollton, MI </li>\n    <li>Cass City Public Schools, Cass City, MI </li>\n    <li>Concord Community Schools, Elkhart, IN </li>\n    <li>Duneland School Corporation, Chesterton, IN </li>\n    <li>Greenfield - Central Community Schools, Greenfield, IN </li>\n    <li>Indianapolis Public Schools, Indianapolis, IN </li>\n    <li>Kalamazoo Regional Educational Services Agency (RESA), Kalamazoo, MI </li>\n    <li>Kent ISD (regional educational service agency), Grand Rapids, MI </li>\n    <li>Michigan Schools Investment Association (MSIA), Lansing, MI </li>\n    <li>Milan Community Schools, Milan, IN </li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>North Gibson School Corporation, Princeton, IN </li>\n    <li>Otsego Public Schools, Otsego, MI </li>\n    <li>Oxford Community Schools, Oxford, MI </li>\n    <li>Paw Paw Public Schools, Paw Paw, MI </li>\n    <li>Portage Public Schools, Portage, MI </li>\n    <li>Rochester Community Schools, Rochester, MI </li>\n    <li>South Gibson School Corporation, Fort Branch, IN </li>\n    <li>St. Johns Public Schools, St. Johns, MI </li>\n    <li>Tell City - Troy Township School Corporation, Tell City, IN </li>\n    <li>Valparaiso Community Schools, Valparaiso, IN </li>\n    <li>Vincennes Community School Corporation, Vincennes, IN </li>\n    <li>Warrick County School Corporation, Boonville, IN</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div id="wide-callout">\n  <h2>Cash Advisory Serivces</h2>\n  <p><a href="http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com" target="_blank">Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC</a> was developed as an independent business entity to help create<br />\n    structured investment programs for our client''s bond proceeds and operating funds.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n  </div><!-- end div #mainColumn -->\n  <div id="sideColumn"> \n    <div id="nav_menu-4" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n      <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n        <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n          <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/services">Our Services</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n	<h2>Latest News goes here</h2>\n			</div><!-- end DIV #sideColumn --> \n		</div><!-- end div .interior-content --> \n	</div><!-- end div #wrapper --> \n{embed=''includes/footer''}'),
(97, 59, 'exp_templates', 'template_data', 1400264342, 1, '{embed=''includes/xhtml'' page_title=""}\n\n{embed=''includes/header''}\n<div class="wrapper">\n<div class="interior-content">\n  <div id="mainColumn" class="services">\n\n\n<h1>Utilities</h1>\n<div id="callout">\n  <h2>Our Experience</h2>\n  <p>The City of Mishawaka''s municipally owned sewage works is working to make a nearly 60-year-old wastewater treatment facility meet federal guidelines of the Clean Water Act.  Umbaugh analyzed various cost scenarios as the utility negotiated with the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA), the U.S. Department of Justice and the Indiana Department of Environmental Management (IDEM) to find a workable solution.</p>\n  <p><a href="/services/our-experience/mishawaka-sewage-works-finding-a-solution-that-works-environmentally-and-fi">Read More &raquo;</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>\n<p>Governmental units are constantly seeking new, better and more cost-effective solutions to the demand for energy and other services. UMBAUGH takes a comprehensive approach that begins with constructing a customized financial plan for your utility. We then effectively and clearly communicate the financial plan to help you get the necessary support to make your plan successful.</p>\n</p>\n<div id="services-table">\n  <h2>Our Services for Utilities</h2>\n  <p>If only it were as simple as turning on a faucet and letting an endless supply of resources flow to customers. But your job as the utility owner gets more difficult every day. Constantly increasing quality standards, new federal mandates and regulatory compliance are just the beginning. When times are good, you must plan ahead to serve more customers to support economic development.  But when customers are closing their doors, you must reduce operations and budgets &#8211; and balance good service with rates your customers can afford.</p>\n  <p><strong>Financial Management</strong> – UMBAUGH can make your day-to-day financial management easier with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Accounting Systems Design, Implementation and Training</li>\n    <li>Audit Preparation and Financial Reporting</li>\n    <li>Financial Planning and Budget Assistance</li>\n    <li>Financial Feasibility Studies</li>\n    <li>Financial Management Reports</li>\n    <li>GASB 34 Compliance</li>\n    <li>Litigation Support Services/Expert Testimony</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Negotiating Inter-Governmental Agreements</li>\n    <li>Performance Management Studies</li>\n    <li>Privatization Analysis</li>\n    <li>Studies of Impact and Fairness in Utility Wholesale Charges</li>\n    <li>Studies Relating to Purchase of Private Utilities by Municipalities</li>\n    <li>Utility Flow-Through Systems Analysis, Fuel Cost Charges and Tracking</li>\n    <li>Utility Rate Studies and Cost-of-Service Analysis</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Capital Planning</strong> &#8211; Utilities are capital-intensive. Like most municipal utilities, you may have aging infrastructure and equipment, need to grow and improve services or need to comply with ever-changing federal and state mandates. You need to find the resources to make those things happen.  UMBAUGH can help you with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Long-Range Capital Planning</li>\n    <li>Project Planning and Financial Development</li>\n    <li>Developing and Evaluating Funding Alternatives</li>\n    <li>Projects Financed by Federal Grants and Loans</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Capital Investment Funding Through System Development Charges</li>\n    <li>Refinancing Existing Debt</li>\n    <li>Financial Presentations to Elected Officials and the Public</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Bond Issuance</strong> &#8211; Your don&#8217;t issue bonds every day, and you&#8217;ve got to get it right. The stakes are too high to risk a mistake or miss an opportunity to save. Since UMBAUGH is an independent advisor, our only priority is doing what&#8217;s best for the municipal and cooperatively -owned utilities we represent. We can provide:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Official Statements and Bond Sale Preparations</li>\n    <li>Presentations to Bond Ratings Agencies</li>\n    <li>Evaluation of Bond Insurance Proposals</li>\n    <li>Competitive Bond Sales and Electronic Bidding Services</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Negotiated Bond Sales and Private Placements</li>\n    <li>Coordination of Bond Closings</li>\n    <li>Assistance to the Trustee bank</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Post Issuance</strong> &#8211; Unfortunately, paperwork does not go away after the bonds are sold. You as the bond issuer have a great deal of responsibility for reporting and compliance, at a time when you&#8217;d much rather pay attention to your bond-funded project. UMBAUGH can take those worries off your plate as well with:</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>In-Progress Construction Reports</li>\n    <li>Arbitrage Rebate Calculations</li>\n    <li>Continuing Disclosure Filings</li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Post Issuance Tax Compliance</li>\n    <li>Escrow Verifications</li>\n    <li>Parity Reports</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div class="two-col-list">\n  <h3>Representative Projects</h3>\n  <p>UMBAUGH has completed over a thousand bond issues ranging from $50,000 to over $500 million.</p>\n  <ul class="left">\n    <li>Brownsburg Municipal Water Utility </li>\n    <li>City of Rensselaer Utilities </li>\n    <li>Evansville Water and Sewer Utility </li>\n    <li>Goshen Municipal Water Utility </li>\n    <li>Jasper Municipal Electric Utility </li>\n  </ul>\n  <ul class="right">\n    <li>Mishawaka Utilities </li>\n    <li>Noblesville Municipal Sewage Works </li>\n    <li>Plainfield Municipal Sewage Works </li>\n    <li>Princeton Municipal Sewage Works </li>\n    <li>Warsaw Municipal Sewage Works</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div id="wide-callout">\n  <h2>Cash Advisory Serivces</h2>\n  <p><a href="http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com" target="_blank">Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC</a> was developed as an independent business entity to help create<br />\n    structured investment programs for our client''s bond proceeds and operating funds.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n  </div><!-- end div #mainColumn -->\n  <div id="sideColumn"> \n    <div id="nav_menu-4" class="widget widget_nav_menu">\n      <div class="menu-sidebar-menu-container">\n        <ul id="menu-sidebar-menu" class="menu">\n          <li id="menu-item-255" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-255"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/services">Our Services</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-64" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-64"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/contact">Contact Us</a></li>\n          <li id="menu-item-65" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-65"><a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/join-our-firm">Join Our Firm</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n	<h2>Latest News goes here</h2>\n			</div><!-- end DIV #sideColumn --> \n		</div><!-- end div .interior-content --> \n	</div><!-- end div #wrapper --> \n{embed=''includes/footer''}');
